subject: entity-manager: Support for DPS310 and SI7020 Rainier
commitMessage:
entity-manager: Support for DPS310 and SI7020 Rainier

Infineon DPS310 pressure and temperature sensors for the
Blyth Front Panel, as well as the Silicon Laboratories
SI7020 type sensors.  Since we used "Name" for temperatures for the
other 2 devices it was simpler to have "Name" for "Ambient 1 Temp"
so swapped with "Station Pressure" and made "Station Pressure"
"Name1".

Tested: busctl tree --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor
busctl introspect --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor \
/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/temperature/Ambient_0_Temp
busctl introspect --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor \
/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/temperature/Ambient_1_Temp
busctl introspect --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor \
/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/temperature/Ambient_2_Temp
busctl introspect --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor \
/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/temperature/PCIE_0_Temp
busctl introspect --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor \
/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/temperature/PCIE_1_Temp
busctl introspect --no-pager xyz.openbmc_project.HwmonTempSensor \
/xyz/openbmc_project/sensors/pressure/Station_Pressure returned
results consistent with location of the Rainier system.

Signed-off-by: Bruce Mitchell <bruce.mitchell@linux.vnet.ibm.com>
Change-Id: Ia21ca1b494cbd3808f2f7c6b30593648aba1eead

Looks like the default poll rate is 500ms, and it looks like both pressure and temp look for the same PollRate.  I guess ideally they could look at separate ones, such as PollRate and PollRate1?  Or PollRatePressure and PollRateTemp.

But if you'd like to do that in the future, then at least maybe use a PollRate of 1 second, which is decent for temp though overkill for our use of pressure.
Roughly like 23 of https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/43410/33/src/IIOMain.cpp resolve this.
That should be line 23 not like 23.

> hey could look at separate ones, such as PollRate and PollRate1?  Or PollRatePressure and PollRateTemp.

My $0.02 is we should avoid names like PollRate and PollRate1. PollRatePressure and PollRateTemp(erature) feel much more informative.

This is lines 23 through line 26 of https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/43410/33/src/IIOSensor.cpp

// pollRates are expressed in seconds
static constexpr float pollRateDefaultTemperature =
    0.997; // 3 msec less than 1 second
static constexpr float pollRateDefaultPressure = 7 * 60; // 7 minutes
that looks good, thanks.
Seems like 'PressureName'/'TemperatureName' or similar would be more descriptive here, but that isn't in the schema (yet), so I'm OK with whatever.
I agree.  Also the examples showed to use Name1, after Name is already used.
